cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the impact of Web search personalisation on professional knowledge work, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). It also touches on issues of algorithmic bias (cs.CY) and information filtering (cs.SI), as well as natural language processing (cs.CL) in terms of the search queries used by the participants. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, and cs.CL.
